Edited:
- `Berreman/OpticalConstructor/OpticalConstructor.Ui/ConstructionView.fs` (edit dispatch + busy/confirm/undo UI)
- `Berreman/OpticalConstructor/OpticalConstructor.Ui/Shell.fs` (attach the async node-solve `Cmd` in the root `update` for the `Construction` busy transitions, marshaled per §0.4)

## Testing plan

Gates that apply to this slice (run in order; first failure short-circuits):
`build`, `unit-tests`, `constructor-unit-tests`, `impl-log-structure`,
`state-of-world-structure`, `ui-smoke`, `ui-tests`.

- `ui-tests`: a headless view test asserts a stack edit dispatches
  `Construction (EditStack …)`, the node shows busy via `isNodeBusy`, the
  `NodeSolved` result refreshes the view with no manual reload (AC-U2.1), and the
  delete-confirm flow appears and removes the sub-tree with undo available
  (AC-U2.2).
- `ui-smoke`: the `stack` panel still renders one frame headlessly.
- `build`, `constructor-unit-tests`, `unit-tests`: green; no frozen edits.

## Risks

- **Medium: off-UI-thread re-solve + marshaling.** The node-solve `Cmd` runs
  `solveSubtree` off the UI thread and must marshal the `NodeSolved` completion
  back onto the UI thread via `Dispatcher.UIThread.Post` (§0.4). A direct
  cross-thread dispatch is a defect; getting the busy→solve→refresh cycle correct
  at per-node granularity is the main worry.

## Hand-off

- The `stack` panel is now fully editable and the async node-solve `Cmd` pattern
  (busy → off-thread solve → marshaled `NodeSolved`) is established; U7's fit
  `Cmd` reuses the same §0.4 marshaling discipline.
- Emit the state-of-the-world `gates:` YAML block with this round's baseline
  counts so the next slice's `count_at_least` gates have a baseline.
